WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.395
In this video I'm going
to show you my seven step

00:00:02.395 --> 00:00:04.616
process for selling with Facebook ads.

00:00:04.616 --> 00:00:06.917
Over the past six months
I've used this exact method

00:00:06.917 --> 00:00:10.155
to generate over 13,000
website conversions

00:00:10.155 --> 00:00:11.738
for just £0.91 each.

00:00:12.727 --> 00:00:15.296
I'm Ben Heath, the Founder
and CEO of Lead Guru,

00:00:15.296 --> 00:00:17.955
which is a London-based
digital marketing agency.

00:00:17.955 --> 00:00:19.647
And today, you're going to learn the seven

00:00:19.647 --> 00:00:22.727
most important keys to success
with Facebook advertising

00:00:22.727 --> 00:00:25.490
so that you can sell your
products and services fast.

00:00:25.490 --> 00:00:26.438
Keep watching.

00:00:31.810 --> 00:00:35.439
I launched my very first
Facebook ad campaign in 2012.

00:00:35.439 --> 00:00:38.770
And since I started, Facebook
advertising has changed a lot.

00:00:38.770 --> 00:00:40.879
Back then there were a lot few advertisers

00:00:40.879 --> 00:00:42.991
and Facebook advertising
was so cheap that you

00:00:42.991 --> 00:00:45.642
could just throw up an ad
and watch the sales roll in.

00:00:45.642 --> 00:00:47.871
Today the platform is
a lot more competitive,

00:00:47.871 --> 00:00:49.701
and that simply won't work.

00:00:49.701 --> 00:00:52.314
Does that mean you should give
up on Facebook advertising?

00:00:52.314 --> 00:00:53.343
Absolutely not!

00:00:53.343 --> 00:00:56.988
Facebook is an amazingly
sophisticated advertising platform.

00:00:56.988 --> 00:00:59.540
And with the seven steps that
I'm going to share with you,

00:00:59.540 --> 00:01:01.279
in this video, you can use it to

00:01:01.279 --> 00:01:04.180
seriously move the needle
and scale your business.

00:01:04.180 --> 00:01:05.410
So without further ado,

00:01:05.410 --> 00:01:07.780
let's get started with
step one, targeting.

00:01:07.780 --> 00:01:10.352
You can create the best
looking ad that's promoting

00:01:10.352 --> 00:01:13.002
an outstanding product, but
none of that will matter

00:01:13.002 --> 00:01:15.384
if you're advertising
it to the wrong people.

00:01:15.384 --> 00:01:16.984
And this is where a
lot of people go wrong.

00:01:16.984 --> 00:01:19.013
Because they think that
targeting is simple.

00:01:19.013 --> 00:01:20.531
They go into their Facebook ad account and

00:01:20.531 --> 00:01:23.307
select interest targetings
that are related

00:01:23.307 --> 00:01:25.056
to the products and
services that they sell.

00:01:25.056 --> 00:01:27.016
But here's the thing,
just because someone is

00:01:27.016 --> 00:01:29.216
interested in something,
doesn't mean they're

00:01:29.216 --> 00:01:30.565
ready to buy it from you.

00:01:30.565 --> 00:01:32.768
There's a huge difference
between advertising

00:01:32.768 --> 00:01:35.244
to people that know you
and people that don't.

00:01:35.244 --> 00:01:37.425
Advertising to people that
have visited your website,

00:01:37.425 --> 00:01:39.673
engaged with your content,
joined your email list,

00:01:39.673 --> 00:01:41.975
or bought from you before,
will always be much

00:01:41.975 --> 00:01:44.865
more effective than
advertising to cold audiences.

00:01:44.865 --> 00:01:46.593
Of course, you can have success

00:01:46.593 --> 00:01:48.415
advertising to cold audiences.

00:01:48.415 --> 00:01:49.755
We do it all the time.

00:01:49.755 --> 00:01:51.425
But the real magic with Facebook ads

00:01:51.425 --> 00:01:54.697
comes from advertising to warm audiences.

00:01:54.697 --> 00:01:57.034
In Facebook, you advertise
to warm audiences

00:01:57.034 --> 00:01:59.055
by using custom audiences.

00:01:59.055 --> 00:02:00.967
There are many different
types of custom audiences

00:02:00.967 --> 00:02:04.457
on Facebook, but my favourite
is Website Custom Audiences.

00:02:04.457 --> 00:02:06.977
And if you're looking to sell
your products and services,

00:02:06.977 --> 00:02:08.308
these are definitely the people

00:02:08.308 --> 00:02:09.827
that you should start targeting.

00:02:09.827 --> 00:02:11.748
Then you can move onto
other custom audiences

00:02:11.748 --> 00:02:14.988
such as your Email List, Page
Engagement Custom Audiences,

00:02:14.988 --> 00:02:18.508
Video View Custom Audiences,
and of course, Page Likes.

00:02:18.508 --> 00:02:20.797
For most companies, these
custom audiences are going

00:02:20.797 --> 00:02:21.679
to be quite small.

00:02:21.679 --> 00:02:24.039
So it's very important
you consistently create

00:02:24.039 --> 00:02:27.068
content and engage with your
target market to add people

00:02:27.068 --> 00:02:29.081
to these custom audiences.

00:02:29.081 --> 00:02:30.801
And if you still have
some budget left over,

00:02:30.801 --> 00:02:33.553
then you should start
targeting cold audiences.

00:02:33.553 --> 00:02:35.833
And later on in this video
I'm going to show you exactly

00:02:35.833 --> 00:02:38.401
how to advertise to cold audiences.

00:02:38.401 --> 00:02:41.801
But now, let's move onto step
two, which is segmentation.

00:02:41.801 --> 00:02:44.243
After step one you know
that you should start

00:02:44.243 --> 00:02:46.743
by advertising to warm audiences.

00:02:46.743 --> 00:02:48.823
Well you can improve
your results even further

00:02:48.823 --> 00:02:51.655
by segmenting those warm audiences.

00:02:51.655 --> 00:02:54.519
Most businesses offer multiple
products and services.

00:02:54.519 --> 00:02:56.641
But when it comes to
advertising to their warm

00:02:56.641 --> 00:02:58.994
audiences on Facebook, they get lazy.

00:02:58.994 --> 00:03:00.766
They use the same ad for everyone,

00:03:00.766 --> 00:03:03.476
which just promotes
one product or service.

00:03:03.476 --> 00:03:05.824
But you'll make a lot
more sales by segmenting

00:03:05.824 --> 00:03:07.657
and it's really easy to do.

00:03:07.657 --> 00:03:10.235
Instead of creating just
one website custom audience

00:03:10.235 --> 00:03:12.966
that includes everyone that
has visited your website,

00:03:12.966 --> 00:03:15.393
you should create website
custom audiences for people

00:03:15.393 --> 00:03:18.564
who have visited specific
pages on your website.

00:03:18.564 --> 00:03:20.463
That way, you can create
separate campaigns

00:03:20.463 --> 00:03:22.883
for different products
and services and in those

00:03:22.883 --> 00:03:24.993
campaigns, only target
people that have visited

00:03:24.993 --> 00:03:27.062
the specific pages on your website

00:03:27.062 --> 00:03:29.513
about those products and services.

00:03:29.513 --> 00:03:31.703
As you can imagine, this
is incredibly effective,

00:03:31.703 --> 00:03:34.183
because if someone has
visited a page on your website

00:03:34.183 --> 00:03:36.463
about a specific product or service,

00:03:36.463 --> 00:03:39.053
they are highly likely
to be interested in it.

00:03:39.053 --> 00:03:41.113
Step three, ad type.

00:03:41.113 --> 00:03:43.028
So which ad type should you use?

00:03:43.028 --> 00:03:45.732
Image ads, video ads, lead ads?

00:03:45.732 --> 00:03:48.793
Unfortunately there's no
one size fits all ad type.

00:03:48.793 --> 00:03:50.903
It really depends on your objective.

00:03:50.903 --> 00:03:52.684
If you want to build
your custom audiences,

00:03:52.684 --> 00:03:55.391
you can use an image ad
that promotes a blog post,

00:03:55.391 --> 00:03:57.249
or a video ad that promotes a video.

00:03:57.249 --> 00:03:58.940
If you're looking to sell
your products and services,

00:03:58.940 --> 00:04:01.231
it really depends on what
you're trying to sell.

00:04:01.231 --> 00:04:03.225
For a relatively small impulse purchase,

00:04:03.225 --> 00:04:04.911
I would probably use an image ad.

00:04:04.911 --> 00:04:07.431
But for a high end or
more complex product,

00:04:07.431 --> 00:04:09.143
I would probably use a video ad.

00:04:09.143 --> 00:04:11.221
The important thing is to experiment,

00:04:11.221 --> 00:04:12.561
and I'm going to show you how to do that

00:04:12.561 --> 00:04:14.671
really easily later in the video.

00:04:14.671 --> 00:04:16.589
Step four, ad creative.

00:04:16.589 --> 00:04:18.503
There are two major parts
to your ad creative.

00:04:18.503 --> 00:04:20.401
You have copy and imagery.

00:04:20.401 --> 00:04:23.855
Both are critical to your
Facebook ad campaign success.

00:04:23.855 --> 00:04:25.845
And each serves a separate purpose.

00:04:25.845 --> 00:04:28.438
Your copy is the part of your
ad that needs to convince

00:04:28.438 --> 00:04:31.949
your audience to take the
action you want them to take.

00:04:31.949 --> 00:04:34.631
Whilst your imagery should
grab your audience's attention

00:04:34.631 --> 00:04:36.549
and represent your brand.

00:04:36.549 --> 00:04:37.879
Let's start with copy.

00:04:37.879 --> 00:04:39.785
It's very important that you tell people

00:04:39.785 --> 00:04:42.764
what your ad is about in
the first couple of lines.

00:04:42.764 --> 00:04:45.071
If your audience needs to
click the see more button

00:04:45.071 --> 00:04:47.682
to see what your ad is for,
then you're in trouble.

00:04:47.682 --> 00:04:50.494
Don't be afraid to
reiterate an important point

00:04:50.494 --> 00:04:51.833
in your ad copy either.

00:04:51.833 --> 00:04:53.423
For example, if you're offering a discount

00:04:53.423 --> 00:04:56.454
include it multiple times,
and absolutely make sure

00:04:56.454 --> 00:04:58.694
people know what the discount is.

00:04:58.694 --> 00:05:00.334
Most people just skim ad copy.

00:05:00.334 --> 00:05:03.334
So what might seem over the
top, almost certainly isn't.

00:05:03.334 --> 00:05:05.624
Also, make sure you
include a call to action.

00:05:05.624 --> 00:05:08.297
And tell people exactly
what you want them to do.

00:05:08.297 --> 00:05:10.756
Should they click on a
link, leave a comment,

00:05:10.756 --> 00:05:12.644
or go through to your
website and purchase?

00:05:12.644 --> 00:05:14.302
Then tell them to do that.

00:05:14.302 --> 00:05:16.184
It sounds obvious, but
I've seen a lot of ads

00:05:16.184 --> 00:05:18.081
without a call to action.

00:05:18.081 --> 00:05:19.583
Let's move on to imagery.

00:05:19.583 --> 00:05:22.048
Two things that have been shown
to grab people's attention

00:05:22.048 --> 00:05:25.030
particularly well are hands and faces.

00:05:25.030 --> 00:05:27.352
Particularly if the face
is making eye contact.

00:05:27.352 --> 00:05:29.576
And this works very well
if you're advertising

00:05:29.576 --> 00:05:31.987
to warm audiences that
would recognise you.

00:05:31.987 --> 00:05:34.043
Obviously images that
include hands and faces

00:05:34.043 --> 00:05:35.695
won't work for every business.

00:05:35.695 --> 00:05:37.719
And honestly, the imagery
that works best for your

00:05:37.719 --> 00:05:39.963
business, may be fairly unique to you.

00:05:39.963 --> 00:05:42.100
For example, some companies
have a lot of success

00:05:42.100 --> 00:05:43.674
using very bright colours.

00:05:43.674 --> 00:05:45.943
The important thing is
that you know the purpose

00:05:45.943 --> 00:05:47.119
of your ads imagery,

00:05:47.119 --> 00:05:49.756
and that is to grab your
audience's attention.

00:05:49.756 --> 00:05:51.863
When you know its purpose you
can test different options

00:05:51.863 --> 00:05:54.620
and find something that
works really well for you.

00:05:54.620 --> 00:05:56.599
And to help you create high converting ads

00:05:56.599 --> 00:05:58.831
that will sell your products or services,

